  dialogueText:
  - 
  - Captain, the ship is ready to launch. Direct trip programmed to Planet Zorbob
    for your meeting with President Blorika.
  - Copy that Commander, hopefully she's in a better mood then she was at our last
    meeting
  - Unlikely sir, the high temperature readings suggest an excessive amount of slime
    secretion for the Zorbobians
  - "*sigh* lets get this over with. Commander, what's the president's file say,
    if she\u2019s gonna be pissy might as well woo her with something, lighten the
    mood, ya know?"
  - The president's Spacebook profile suggests she enjoys long walks on the beach,
    and the sound of people chewing with their mouths open.
  - "I guess I'll have to take what I can get\u2026"
  - 'As you dock at the Space Station orbiting Blorfengarl, the ship opens up to
    a large docking bay. To greet you is a grumpy wad of goo, a spiffy looking tie
    around his neck. '
  - "Ah! Captain... You look so\u2026 intelligent. It\u2019s a pleasure to finally
    be meeting you!"
  - "Pleasure\u2019s all mine General!"
  - Your trip here was alright?
  - Good to hear!
  - HA! Apologies Captain, we meant no harm! We're due on a new Fnozzle for the artificial
    gravity core!
  - "It\u2019s no trouble, just make sure it\u2019s better for next time HAHA!!"
  - Hmm, well we have some Bleeding Grapes back at the Space Station you can have
    some of those.
  - The general turns away, a wet slurping sounds as he moves.
  - Walk with me Captain. The president is waiting in her office.
  - "By the time you make it to the President's Office, you\u2019re tugging at your
    collar, the heat making your shirt stick to your skin. When you open the door
    to the president's office, she is far from what you expected."
  - "She\u2019s a tall green skinned woman with big bug eyes, and dressed much too
    scandalously for a politician."
  - Oh wow! You're earlier than I was anticipating! You must be the captain!
  - She holds out her hand for you to shake.
  - "It\u2019s a pleasure to officially meet you Miss President."
  - "Oh please, I get enough formality from my glorbs\_ everyday, Politicia is fine."
  - Well it's a pleasure to meet you Politicia!
  - Likewise captain!
  - Politicia's outstretched hand freezes before it returns to her side.
  - "Sorry! You\u2019re just\u2026 uh\u2026 very tall."
  - I get that a lot.
  - "Well it\u2019s a pleasure to officially meet you Miss President"
  - Just Politicia is fine.
  - "Politicia's outstretched hand freezes before it returns to her side. Her lips
    purse together as if she\u2019s not sure what to say."
  - "uhh, yea\u2026 I won the election 3 terms in a row"
  - "oh! No that\u2019s not what I meant! You're just like\u2026"
  - like what? (lowkey annoyed)
  - You're not gooey!
  - What does that have to do with anything?! I thought you people were more open-minded
    then that!
  - Politicia is almost fuming. You tug at your collar uncomfortably before taking
    a deep breath.
  - "Clearly we\u2019ve gotten off on the wrong foot haha! All I meant if you look
    different then the rest of your people."
  - "Clearly we have\u2026"
  - Politicia huffs and crosses her arms, obviously offended.
  - uhh, sorry, didn't mean it that way (sweats)
  - I suppose I can ignore this, considering you bring me an offering next time we
    have a meeting.
  - "An uncomfortable silence falls over the two of you. Of course the first time
    you reach out to a new System and you've insulted their President within the
    first minute\u2026"
  - "So uhh\u2026"
  - "Anyways, now that you're here I\u2019d like to discuss the implications of the
    alliance proposal you sent over?"
  - 'Absolutely. The Human Federation have been growing and expanding and as the
    leader of the Raven Galaxy Exploratory Mission, I am looking to make some new
    allies! '
  - "Well, we are looking for some new strong allies, I\u2019m just not quite sure
    we can trust the humans quite yet, no offense!"
  - None taken!
  - "Considering you\u2019ve only established yourselves as a galactic empire fairly
    recently\u2026 I just am unsure of your human history."
  - "That\u2019s a fair concern, but just as a completely unbiased opinion, this
    Human is 100% trustworthy!"
  - You and Politicia take some time going over the alliance proposal, discussing
    details and other political mumbo jumbo, the usual kinds of conversations a politician
    would have.
  - Well, I have a lot to consider for our next meeting!
  - You take her hand, flash a cunning smirk before kissing her spikey knuckles like
    a proper gentlecaptain.
  - I look forward to our next meeting Politicia
  - "Oh my! Don\u2019t be a stranger, Captain!"
  - "I agree, there\u2019s nothing wrong with wanting more allies."
  - Until next time Politicia.
  - Of course, safe travels.
  - The End
  - 
  - "Your eyes have not had a chance to rest since you\u2019ve boarded the ship.
    Even as you stir from your sleep, a cacophony of bright oranges assault your
    vision, only interrupted by an errant shock of white or earthy brown."
  - Your feet hover over the floating edge of your bed, the quiet whishing of your
    R00mbotTM vacuuming softly under your bed threatening to lull you back to sleep.
  - The soft carpeted flooring as you stand and stare at the stars growing ever distant
    out from your large circular window and sigh.
  - The carpet continues into the hallway, though lines lead those less experienced
    with the ship to its various sections and amenities.
  - The Diplomatic Liner-A1LYU80V-8469 has been your home of choice for years now. 
    You have grown so close to her that the two of you share a call-sign, Amore.
  - As you head to your destination you are stopped by a group of large hulking masses
    of misshapen clay as they cross your path.
  - Ignoring you, they stomp off in a hurry, one of the ship's many robots follows
    them, cleaning off the dust and chipping in its path.
  - The softly blinking lights of the bridge copy the shining stars out the massive
    bow-facing windows. A number of figures are waiting for you in the command center,
    your new crew if you had to hazard a guess.
  - To your left a woman is rapping her knuckles against one of the consoles, swaying
    nervously to the knocks.
  - Next to her another woman is staring at a tablet, leaning against the same console,
    a series of yellow holographic rings emanating from one of her eyes.
  - Down further into the bridge you see a person asleep in an egg-shaped chair,
    one of those clay beasts hunkered over them.
  - In fact a number of these creatures are found all through the lower levels of
    the bridge, attending to odd tasks and shuffling about with purpose.
  - Lastly to your left you find a strange Lepidopteran creature, clipboard in hand,
    looking at you attentively.
  - Before you have a chance to greet them, the lights flash briefly to signal an
    incoming message.
  - From the center of the room a hologram of your commanding officer is displayed,
    their blue-light form flickering periodically.
  - "Ah, I see you\u2019re all here."
  - Their voice crackles with the instability of ultra-long range transmission
  - Captain, the fight against the heathen steLLarITM corporation is set to open
    on a new frontier.
  - We AstranautsTM must quickly shore up some support in this star system to ensure
    the local populace is receptive to our products and our values of freedom and
    commerce.
  - We must join forces to win in the free market of ideas and also violence.
  - The commander salutes with pride, but only you and the winged creature actually
    join him.
  - I am familiar with your, uhm-
  - If someone's face could turn red over the blue-tinged display of a hologram,
    you would swear your captain was blushing vigorously.
  - -specialized maneuvers, Captain Amore of the Amore.
  - You are cleared to use any and all methods to enter these xenoform societies
    and bring them into the welcoming bosom of AstratechTM corporation and the wider
    sacred AstraTM conglomerate.
  - In their infinite generosity, our corporate sponsors granted the use of a small
    crew to help you help out on your mission
  - "(Because they aren\u2019t eligible for union membership)"
  - The first of which is Pu Ai, an excellent explorer and xenobiologist.
  - (as a recipient of a scholarship program she is an indentured citemployee until
    she pays of her student loan debt)
  - "The anxious woman at your left looks up to you and smiles, though you wouldn\u2019t
    call it reassuring."
  - Joining her is her longtime companion, Shira Rahman. A brilliant transfer from
    our competitally, AstraSystemsTM, her cyborg enhancements make her a brilliant
    mind to have on any expedition.
  - (and fortunately technically not fully an organic or inorganic mind and therefore
    not eligible for coverage by either guild)
  - The other woman does not look up from her tablet.
  - We also have Judah Ben Loew and his group of glamim to meet any labour or mystical
    needs you may have.
  - "\_(His ability to provide great quantities of unpaid labour has earned the ire
    of workers with rights everywhere)"
  - "The golem watching over their creator\u2019s sleeping form waves at you."
  - Lastly, Marie Posa, a LepidJanussian, is here to serve you as your ship's communications
    officer.
  - (Do not let her get tired or you will meet her worse half and learn why her species
    is considered too volatile for solidarity with other citemployees)
  - The one non-human in the room nods at you, a sign of deference you believe, as
    her face is otherwise inscrutable.
  - "Now I\u2019ve been ordered to test your ability to command your crew members
    after your last mut-, incident kerfuffle. Please select Judah and Shira to assist
    you in this training exercise."
  - 
  - Wonderful!
  - "The captain\u2019s tone is overly saccharine and rigid as though reading from
    a script."
  - Now use their combined brain power to solve this simple logic puzzle
  - "You're amazing. Now use Shira\u2019s Science knowledge to help defeat the negative
    thoughts in this mental exercise."
  - Wow, great job, me and other surrogate parental figures are proud of you.
  - Now remember even though your crew members are third class citemployees and are
    therefore exempt from traditional labour laws, overuse of your employees can
    lead to a depreciation of value for your human resources.
  - With the completion of this module you are now recertified to undertake missions
    for the glorious AstraTM conglomerate. Good luck Captain!
  - "You see the commander fiddle with something on his desk. Quietly you can make
    out. \u201CAstra\u2019sTM Excellent Value, that\u2019s over. How do I turn this
    off?\u201D"
  - "Your commander\u2019s face disappears from the bridge and your crew members
    wait on your word. You have your orders."
  - 
  - Incorrect, please pick Judah and Shira to continue;
  - 
  - The Amore charts its course to the first planet on your alliance-building mission.
    Ai opens the AstratechTM file on the main console.
  - Blorfengarl, a planet with an intense gravitational pull. Its dominant lifeform
    is a mucusoid species known as blorforms.
  - Initially hostile to earlier exploratory missions, they have since built and
    launched an orbital station named Membrane on which to receive guests.
  - You make your approach to this round, bubble-shaped spacestation. Docking into
    a large ship-bay, you are struck by a wave of hot air as the humidity seeps through
    your clothing.
  - "Vents and spherical outcropping dot the hall, and despite its emptiness you
    can\u2019t shake the feeling of being watched. "
  - Have your crew forgotten to announce themselves beforehand? Your call echoes
    around the bay before the sound of gurgling at your feet draws your gaze downwards.
  - The vents and spherical outcroppings have windows and holes. Strange for the
    purposes of ventilation but less so for the purpose of cautiously viewing.
  - 'As mucusoids blorforms should easily be able to pass through grates and fit
    their bodies into tight spaces. As if on cue a gurgling at the grate beneath
    your feet proves your hypothesis. '
  - Despite your best efforts you find yourself simply looking back and forth futilely.
    You still cannot shake the feeling of being watched. You jump as you are startled
    by a gurgling at your feet.
  - Out from a grate, green viscous fluid begins to pour forth. It arranges itself
    into the dumpy form, rolls on top of rolls cascaded down this standing puddle
    of a creature.
  - Its body a sickly green, a single lashed eyestalk peers forth as its other eye
    floats aimlessly through the main body.
  - "Its mouth was more similar to a relief carved onto a sculpture or pastry, the
    slab-like teeth barely more defined than the indented \u201Cmouth\u201D that
    helped them."
  - It altogether seems unnatural for a creature that can simply schlorp its body
    around anything it wishes to consume.
  - In a way it is almost cute, a gesture to elicit some goodwill from the foreigners
    it is greeting. A medal floats in its transparent body, on it a name inscribed.
    General Goumyster.
  - "Ah! Captain... You look so\u2026 intelligent. It\u2019s a pleasure to finally
    be meeting you!"
  - "The general\u2019s voice is strange and garbled, like someone trying to speak
    with a full mouth or underwater."
  - Through the distortion you can detect a note of discomfort, is the species unaccustomed
    to verbal conversation or are they somehow already displeased with you in some
    way.
  - "Pleasure\u2019s all mine General!"
  - No matter. As an AstraTechTM certified diplomacy captain and brand ambassador
    you are adept at navigating tricky situations to ensure an optimal outcome for
    all stakeholders.
  - Your trip here was alright?
  - "A question, an opportunity. You can attempt to use your advanced negotiative
    techniques you\u2019ve been perfecting all the way from Advertising Yourself
    101, back in your cadet days."
  - Positivity. AstraInsiderTM has stated for years that people in positions of authority
    enjoy relentless enthusiasm, happiness, and satisfaction from their subordinates
    and those that they encounter elsewhere.
  - For the greater good of your corporation, nay your conglomerate, you will adopt
    the submissive position.
  - Lulling them into a sense of security and satisfaction can make future negotiations
    lean towards favorable outcomes for your party.
  - Good to hear!
  - Tension. Though verbalizing discomfort is not technically permitted under the
    AstraTechTM employee charter, in your role as captain you are permitted to bend
    the rules a bit in order to foster a greater sense of emotional proximity with
    your potential clients.
  - You have observed on occasion lower-level employees bonding over the shared commiseration
    of misfortunes and ills of all manners.
  - Additionally the discomfort posed by displeasure may momentarily disarm your
    opponent, affording you better leverage in future negotiations.
  - HA! Apologies Captain, we meant no harm! We're due for a new Fnozzle for the
    artificial gravity core!
  - "The General\u2019s form starts swaying aggressively as their transparent interior
    produces plumes of bubbles and froth. Anger? Fear? Embarrassment?"
  - Now did you mean to accuse or cause offence with your words? It is of no importance,
    they have shown their belly and you are ready to pounce.
  - "It\u2019s no trouble, just make sure it\u2019s better for next time HAHA!!"
  - "The General\u2019s swaying has grown ever more frantic as if they can\u2019t
    wait to move. SUCCESS? You have made this stranger uncomfortable."
  - Humour. A charming anecdote that would prove to be supremely relatable and well
    received. Humour is the basis of many an excellent advertisement.
  - It is memorable and can be repeated in the future to strengthen positive memories
    of the experience. Yes, the perfect approach to disarm your opponent for future
    investigations.
  - 'The General unleashes a violent jiggle before composing themself. You see a
    flash of hunger in their eyes, the same ravenous hunger that binds all life forms
    and thrusts them forward. '
  - The burning that can only be satisfied with a range of delicious, nutritious,
    and affordable foodstuffs purchasable in any friendly canteen.
  - hmm, well we have some Bleeding Grapes back at the Space Station you can have
    some of those.
  - The general turns away, a wet slurping sound fills the bay, as they drag their
    body on the floor, leaving a sticky green trail behind them.
  - Walk with me Captain. The president is waiting in her office.
  - President? The general has an attending superior? Have you wasted your excellent
    social skills on a mere underling?
  - "Those are valuable billable hours you have spent suboptimally. Fortunately you
    yourself\_ don\u2019t have a supervisor present, otherwise your wages may be
    garnished for such an offence."
  - "By the time you make it to the President's Office, you\u2019re tugging at your
    collar, the heat making your shirt stick to your skin. When you open the door
    to the president's office, she is far from what you expected."
  - "Humanoid in shape, she\u2019s a tall green skinned woman with big compound eyes.
    The lights of the space station reflect and shine off them like the hazy glow
    of a distant city at night."
  - While dressed far too scandalously for your expectations of a politician, you
    are more shocked by her species.
  - She is clearly not a blorform. Odd that such a traditionally reclusive and hostile
    species has elected a foreigner to oversee these negotiations.
  - The general shuffles off, but the strange feeling that you are being watched
    does not follow him out.
  - Oh wow! You're earlier than I was anticipating! You must be the captain!
  - 
